    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a subfamily containing 12 living species of solitary marsh birds, allied to the heron, but with shorter neck and stouter body. Bitterns typically have a camouflage pattern of streaks of variegated brown and buff, and when they stand with their bill pointed upwards they are able dissappear among the reeds and grasses of their habitat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
